*drumroll* 
We just launched a range of Supperr Siilkkyy & Smoooth Date-Sweetened Milk Chocolates. 

No added sugar. No artificial sweeteners. No compound. No added chocolate flavour. No preservatives. 

————

‘I have to get every ingredient right. There’s nowhere to hide.’

If you’re a MasterChef fan, you’ve heard this line from contestants making a dish with just 2-3 ingredients. At TWT, this line is life. Allow us to explain. 

Next time when you’re in the market, pick up a pack of your favourite chocolate & turn to read the ingredients. 

First up, chances are the first ingredient is Refined Sugar, which means it’s the largest by constitution. Yikes. 

Next, funnily, you’ll hardly find ‘cocoa beans or cocoa’ as an ingredient. Instead there's ‘chocolate compound’. 

What is compound? Well, it’s a mix of cocoa + vegetable fat + sweeteners. Ideally, chocolate should be made with cocoa butter. But that’s expensive. Vegetable fat like palm-oil is cheap. Hence, compound. 

Besides, real chocolate needs tempering. That’s a very delicate and technical process of heating & cooling liquid chocolate to exact temperatures to stabilise & set. Again, time consuming & expensive. So yeahhh. 

Perfectly tempered chocolate is shiny, has a great snap, and it melts in your mouth. But hey, that means it melts in transit, in warehouses, and in non-AC retail stores too. Unlike compound, which doesn’t even melt at 45°C. So what if it’s a little harder to digest since it takes a while to melt in your stomach!

Apart from compound, commercial chocolate might have the usual culprits. Preservatives, emulsifiers, ingredients with numbers...you get the gist. 

And oh, it might also have added flavours like vanilla and…wait for it…chocolate. Yes, your chocolate has chocolate flavour. Beat that!

Alllll this.. we couldn’t. We’re not that smart. We like to keep things simple. 

So we made our chocolates with just 3 ingredients. Cocoa, Dates, Whole milk powder. We spent 18 months perfecting the recipe. Because we’re sworn to declaring each and every ingredient on the front of pack. So, just like in Masterchef, we have nowhere to hide. And neither do we wish to.

Yahaan main pighal gaya.

.

.

.

*drumroll* Launching India’s First Date-Sweetened Dark Chocolates!

Oh and we mean real, coverture, bean-to-bar chocolate. Not that chemical and vegetable oil laden compound most big-guys use. Allow us to explain. 

Have you ever wondered why some chocolates never melt? .Not even in a kirana store in peak Indian summers!

Well, you’re right to wonder. Because real chocolate *does* melt. If it doesn’t, you can safely assume it’s compound. Why?

Well because real chocolate has cocoa butter. And when given some warmth and love (anything from Delhi summers to a few seconds on your tongue should work), it readily melts into a decadent puddle of love. 

Any ‘chocolate’ that doesn’t, feel free to believe that the nutrient rich cocoa butter has been replaced with hydrogenated edible fats and is loaded with chemicals and stabilisers. In other words - it’s compound.

Fun fact: Compound was earlier known as mock chocolate or coating chocolate. It came into existence as a coating for real (couverture) chocolate. Because real chocolate just doesn’t have the shine and stability of compound. 

Anyways, everything at The Whole Truth is, as always…Simple. Not compound. 

Two ingredients. Kerala cocoa. Sweetened with dates. Bean-to-bar. All in-house. So we know exactly what’s going into your chocolate. 

Simple. Real. Food. 

PS: Next time you’re buying chocolate, ask yourself. If the good old Indian summers can’t melt it, how will your body?

*drumroll* The Whole Truth is we’re launching India’s First Date-Sweetened Dark Chocolate!!!

Yup, sweetened *only* with dates. No Added Sugaaaaaa! 

No chemicals and no fake photos eithaaa! That’s what all this has been building up to. Read on!

——————————

Some people think we’re a snack brand. Some others assume we’re a ‘Healthy’ Food company. But, truth be told, we see ourselves as a truth company. Our mission - to bring truth back to food. To make food real again. 

And real food, by definition, can’t be ‘healthy’ or ‘unhealthy’. Infact if you’ve been following our recent ad-series, you’d know how much we loathe this word ‘healthy’. It’s the food marketeers biggest weapon, because no one knows what it means. Esp when it’s applied to whole categories of food!

Pizzas are unhealthy. Soups are healthy. Chocolate is unhealthy. Protein bars are healthy. Huh, right. We wouldn’t need to exist if they were. 

Truth is, food isn’t inherently healthy or unhealthy. And neither are the people who eat it. The same person eats a protein bar after working out in the morning, and then ends their day with a piece of chocolate. Or two. Depending on how harsh the day’s been.

If that sounds like you, then hey, welcome to the club. The club of normal people. People who love chocolate (who doesn’t?). And people who try real hard to eat clean, nutritious food, everyday. We see you, and we did this for you. 

It took us 18 months, and countless iterations, to clean up chocolate. Along the way, many asked us - aren’t you a healthy food company? Aren’t you going tooo far, entering a category as indulgent and ‘unhealthy’ as chocolate?

Well, they were right about one thing. We did go too far. From setting up our own bean-to-bar facility, to ethically sourcing the best beans directly from farmers, to spending months and months getting the taste right - we went further than we’ve ever gone before, to clean up our one, true indulgence. Chocolate. 

So come, join us on this journey, as we take you behind the scenes on what it took to make India’s first, date-sweetened chocolate. 

Cheers
Team @ The Whole Truth

*drumroll*
 
Introducing the cleanest, yummiest range of plant proteins. Ever.
Starting with, ofcourse, Double-Cocoa.
 
Our first bar was Double Cocoa. Our highest selling one too. And it should come as no surprise that across the protein industry, ‘chocolate’ is the highest selling flavor by far. So it would seem like making a chocolate flavored plant protein should be easy (everyone does it, after all). 

Nothing could be further from the truth. For two reasons.
 
One, you want your chocolate shake to be creamy. But plant protein isn’t milky or creamy (duh). That’s why many brands add coconut or almond milk powder, to get that creaminess. Unfortunately, we couldn’t find any plant-based milk powder, at scale, that doesn’t have a bulking agent like Maltodextrin. So we chucked it.
 
Next, for brands that are ok using  ‘nature-identical’ flavors (remember, chocolate doesn’t grow on a tree, cocoa does) - they can just drop a few drops of it in your protein and voila, chocolate flavor delivered.
 
But real cocoa isn’t as flavor-packed as a concocted chocolate flavoring agent. And hence, to get the chocolatiness you’d want from your shake, we had to use a lot of it. A WHOLE lot. 20% of our recipe is just cocoa. And cocoa is damn expensive. Hmmm…now there’s a clue as to why so few use it.
 
So yea, that’s what it takes to make a clean, mean, chocolate plant protein. One that makes your tongue go yumms and keeps you happy in the tumms. 
 
Try it. Tell us if it makes you go coco-loco. Use code HAINITERACOCOA and get as much off your first purchase, as there is cocoa in your protein. 20%, to be clear :)

Labels, unlike hips, do lie.
Plant protein is chalky.
 
Just some statements of fact we’ve all learnt to live with. Well, the last one ends today. Presenting a plant protein that is far less gritty and grainy than its predecessors.
 
How?
 
Well it starts with suuper fine grade protein isolates sourced from Canada and Europe. And it ends with…ha! nice try. It ends with you watching this video and using code YOUSOFINE to get 10% off your first purchase. Let’s go!

You planted the idea. And here it is!
 
*drumroll*
 
Introducing the cleanest, yummiest range of plant protein. Ever! 
 
Ever since we launched our cleanest, lightest whey - so many of you have asked us to do the same for plant protein. And God knows we’ve been trying. God also knows it’s one of the tougher problems he’s given human-kind (easier than Trump though).
 
The problem starts with texture and mouthfeel. Plant protein, by nature, is so chalky and gritty, it can feel like having mud. We feel you.
 
Next comes flavour. Peas, chickpeas, hemp, rice - no matter the source, the grainy taste of the protein has a way of over-powering any other flavor. Of course, as is standard in the food industry, many brands try to solve this by adding “nature-identical” flavours and artificial sweeteners. Which makes the problem worse. Because now it is overly sweet and has that strange, metallic after-taste too.
 
And last, there’s the question of efficacy. Is plant protein as effective at muscle building as whey? Is it a complete protein? Most plant based sources, standalone, are not.
 
No wonder it took a while nailing this. But we did. Here’s how.
 
First, we travelled the globe and found a suuuper fine grade of golden pea protein isolate. Aka, very fine particle size to begin with. And hence, much lower chalkiness. BIG WIN!
 
Next, we mixed pea and brown rice protein isolates in a 70:30 ratio. Pea protein is rich in lysine but poor in methionine. Brown rice is the exact opposite. But mix them right, and you get a complete protein. One that has all 9 essential amino acids in the right quantities. YASS!
 
And last, we obviously used real ingredients. Real dark cocoa. Real pista and badaam flakes. Real apple beetroot and carrot (yes, you heard that right!)

It took all this, and a whole lot of trial and error (right sourcing, right recipe proportions, right mixing process, right quality controls) - to make this Clean Plant Protein Actually Tasty.
 
But don’t take our word for it. Try it. Don’t know which flavor to try? Get the All in one sampler and then decide. Use code EASYPEASY and get 10% off. Tell us if it made you go No Whey!

My dad was doing everything right- lifting weights, eating clean, but he still wasn’t getting stronger.

What changed? Sarcopenia.

What is Sarcopenia?
It is the gradual loss of muscle and strength that naturally comes with age, and if left unaddressed, it can seriously affect daily life.
It can lead to:
 – Higher risk of metabolic issues like diabetes
 – Slower recovery from illness or surgery
 – Increased risk of falls and fractures 
 – Struggles with everyday tasks like climbing stairs or carrying bags

BUT

Sarcopenia can be slowed - even reversed- with the right strength training and high-protein nutrition.

We added chicken, fish, eggs, and one scoop of whey protein from @thewholetruthfoods every day. And that changed everything.
Their whey is a game changer:
 ✅ Light on the stomach
 ✅ No bloating or indigestion
 ✅ Just clean ingredients — no preservatives, no junk
It’s perfect for parents who need more protein but can’t handle the heavy stuff.

BREAKING BREAD. Let’s really break this down. You have brown bread. And atta bread. And whole wheat bread. And oh no, there’s also 100% whole wheat bread. All you want is to buy nutritious bread. And what you get… clunky, confusing claims.

This is by design. Marketers know exactly what they are doing. That’s why brown bread has brown color. And atta bread has maida. And whole wheat is not “whole” wheat.

But hey, there’s no need to get paranoid. What matters is knowing what you are eating. Choose the best among available options. And then pair it with proteins, fats, and fiber to make a wholesome meal.

Watch our video to find out… the whole truth about bread.
